and the crappy paycheck,

323
00:14:25,821 --> 00:14:27,214
it comes with the job.

324
00:14:27,257 --> 00:14:28,911
- Then why don't you help me
do something about it?

325
00:14:28,955 --> 00:14:30,739
- I may have a title
that sounds effectual,

326
00:14:30,782 --> 00:14:33,394
but I have absolutely no power.

327
00:14:33,437 --> 00:14:36,223
I can't help you do anything.

328
00:14:44,405 --> 00:14:46,798
- "I think that tears
are a sign of weakness."

329
00:14:46,842 --> 00:14:48,322
- Agree.

330
00:14:48,365 --> 00:14:51,803
- "I think that other people's
feelings are not important."

331
00:14:51,847 --> 00:14:52,979
- Agree.

332
00:14:55,285 --> 00:14:58,071
- "I think about
hurting my family."

333
00:14:58,114 --> 00:14:59,768
- Agree.

334
00:15:02,379 --> 00:15:04,773
- Just your brother?

335
00:15:04,816 --> 00:15:06,818
Who else?

336
00:15:06,862 --> 00:15:09,082
- My mom and dad.

337
00:15:09,125 --> 00:15:10,561
- Why do you want to hurt them?

338
00:15:13,477 --> 00:15:14,957
- Because I can.

339
00:15:24,314 --> 00:15:26,055
- You know, I mean, it's early,

340
00:15:26,099 --> 00:15:29,537
and one session
is a small sample, but, uh,

341
00:15:29,580 --> 00:15:32,453
Juliet does present
as callous-unemotional.

342
00:15:34,281 --> 00:15:36,109
- You're saying
she's a psychopath.

343
00:15:40,940 --> 00:15:42,942
- She's been to dozens
of doctors.

344
00:15:42,985 --> 00:15:46,032
We've heard schizophrenia,
ADHD, RAD.

345
00:15:46,075 --> 00:15:48,730
No one's ever said "psychopath."

346
00:15:48,773 --> 00:15:50,862
- Callous-unemotional.

347
00:15:50,906 --> 00:15:52,473
It's, um--it's not a diagnosis

348
00:15:52,516 --> 00:15:54,170
that doctors really
like to give because,

349
00:15:54,214 --> 00:15:56,433
historically speaking,

350
00:15:56,477 --> 00:15:58,827
there is no cure.

351
00:15:58,870 --> 00:16:01,134
- Then what do we do?
- Well...

352
00:16:01,177 --> 00:16:03,701
- She'll go into
an inpatient facility

353
00:16:03,745 --> 00:16:06,748
run by
the corrections department.

354
00:16:06,791 --> 00:16:09,707
- Jail?
She's 11.

355
00:16:09,751 --> 00:16:13,233
- Hold on, hold on, hold on.
There is one other possibility.

356
00:16:13,276 --> 00:16:17,759
Um, punishment bounces off
of callous-unemotional kids

357
00:16:17,802 --> 00:16:20,022
because they can't feel shame,

358
00:16:20,066 --> 00:16:22,807
but there has been some very
promising behavioral therapy

359
00:16:22,851 --> 00:16:24,984
based on a reward system.

360
00:16:25,027 --> 00:16:26,942
I'm sure you've noticed
Juliet's reward drive

361
00:16:26,986 --> 00:16:28,248
is extremely high.

362
00:16:28,291 --> 00:16:31,120
That's why she takes
whatever she wants.

363
00:16:31,164 --> 00:16:35,255
So if I can demonstrate
some progress with Juliet,

364
00:16:35,298 --> 00:16:37,039
we can admit her here.

365
00:16:37,083 --> 00:16:39,302
She could be an inpatient
at New Amsterdam.

366
00:16:40,956 --> 00:16:43,089
- Dr. Frome?
- Yeah.

367
00:16:43,132 --> 00:16:46,266
- Have you ever had success
with a child like Juliet?

368
00:16:52,881 --> 00:16:54,143
- No.

369
00:17:06,112 --> 00:17:07,200
- You okay?

370
00:17:07,243 --> 00:17:10,420
- Sex.

371
00:17:10,464 --> 00:17:14,381
I just replaced pills with sex.

372
00:17:14,424 --> 00:17:16,948
I would say that
I make the worst decisions,

373
00:17:16,992 --> 00:17:18,167
but you know what?

374
00:17:18,211 --> 00:17:19,908
I'm not even sure
that I make decisions.

375
00:17:19,951 --> 00:17:21,214
I just do things.

376
00:17:21,257 --> 00:17:23,433
- Why is that bad?

377
00:17:23,477 --> 00:17:26,262
If all of your instincts
tell you to do something,

378
00:17:26,306 --> 00:17:27,785
why shouldn't you do that?

379
00:17:27,829 --> 00:17:30,049
My instincts told me

380
00:17:30,092 --> 00:17:33,922
to bang my physical therapist,
and it is not going well.

381
00:17:33,965 --> 00:17:36,142
I thought I was
distracting myself

382
00:17:36,185 --> 00:17:39,101
from the pain,
but you know, actually,

383
00:17:39,145 --> 00:17:42,931
I think I was distracting
myself from being sober.

384
00:17:44,280 --> 00:17:46,456
You know what?
Enough is enough.

385
00:17:46,500 --> 00:17:50,286
God, it is time
to face reality--

386
00:17:50,330 --> 00:17:53,289
to stop avoiding
and start making decisions

387
00:17:53,333 --> 00:17:55,248
that are actually good for me,

388
00:17:55,291 --> 00:17:58,120
like go to an NA meeting.

389
00:17:58,164 --> 00:18:02,298
- You just got
all of that from meditating?

390
00:18:02,342 --> 00:18:04,126
- Yeah.

391
00:18:04,170 --> 00:18:05,954
That is how it works, right?

392
00:18:14,354 --> 00:18:15,964
Yeah?

393
00:18:16,007 --> 00:18:17,444
No.

394
00:18:17,487 --> 00:18:20,360
- Not here to harass you.
I'm just here to apologize.

395
00:18:20,403 --> 00:18:23,145
- You are?
- Yes.

396
00:18:23,189 --> 00:18:26,322
And to find out
what office your boss is in.

397
00:18:26,366 --> 00:18:28,629
- You can't be serious.
- Face to face.

398
00:18:28,672 --> 00:18:30,500
It's gotta be worth something.

399
00:18:30,544 --> 00:18:32,894
- Tenth floor, 1021.
- 1021?

400
00:18:32,937 --> 00:18:34,548
- Mm-hmm.
- Thank you.

401
00:18:36,419 --> 00:18:38,334
So at New Amsterdam,
we run into

402
00:18:38,378 --> 00:18:41,250
arcane policy inconsistencies
all the time.

403
00:18:41,294 --> 00:18:43,513
For example, Frances--
may I call you Frances?

404
00:18:43,557 --> 00:18:45,472
- I'd rather you didn't.
- Okay, sure.

405
00:18:45,515 --> 00:18:49,389
For example, there is
a very expensive spinal surgery

406
00:18:49,432 --> 00:18:51,173
that is covered
by your base policy,

407
00:18:51,217 --> 00:18:54,916
yet there is another procedure
that is less expensive

408
00:18:54,959 --> 00:18:58,180
and less invasive that is not.

409
00:18:58,224 --> 00:19:00,400
And that means that
Barcroft is, in turn,

410
00:19:00,443 --> 00:19:03,533
shelling out more money
than it has to.

411
00:19:03,577 --> 00:19:06,188
My patient, Paz Aquino--
- Account number?

412
00:19:06,232 --> 00:19:09,191
- It's 42118.

413
00:19:12,455 --> 00:19:14,065
- Her claim was denied

414
00:19:14,109 --> 00:19:16,372
because Barcroft
no longer covers surrogacy.

415
00:19:16,416 --> 00:19:18,374
- So I've heard,
but Barcroft will cover

416
00:19:18,418 --> 00:19:20,071
a uterus transplant for her,

417
00:19:20,115 --> 00:19:23,379
which is a procedure
that will cost ten times more.

418
00:19:23,423 --> 00:19:25,207
So, uh,
I guess what I'm saying is,

419
00:19:25,251 --> 00:19:28,645
if Barcroft doesn't want to
reverse its policy on surrogacy,

420
00:19:28,689 --> 00:19:31,257
then I am gonna have
to advise all of my patients

421
00:19:31,300 --> 00:19:34,216
to consider
uterine transplants instead.

422
00:19:34,260 --> 00:19:36,262
And how do you think that's
gonna affect your bottom line?

423
00:19:36,305 --> 00:19:37,698
- That's a good point.

424
00:19:37,741 --> 00:19:40,962
Maybe we should stop covering
uterine transplants

425
00:19:41,005 --> 00:19:42,398
starting now.

426
00:19:44,618 --> 00:19:46,533
Hm.

427
00:19:46,576 --> 00:19:49,231
- No, it is not covered--
- Hi, so sorry.

428
00:19:49,275 --> 00:19:51,538
Can you tell me who her boss is?

429
00:19:52,974 --> 00:19:55,977
- You have a condition called
supraventricular tachycardia.

430
00:19:56,020 --> 00:19:58,284
It's an atypically fast
heartbeat that develops when

431
00:19:58,327 --> 00:20:01,243
the heart's normal electrical
impulses are disrupted,

432
00:20:01,287 --> 00:20:03,550
and the frequency
of the palpitations

433
00:20:03,593 --> 00:20:05,116
forced your kidneys
into overdrive,

434
00:20:05,160 --> 00:20:06,466
which overwhelmed your bladder.

435
00:20:06,509 --> 00:20:07,945
- How do we fix it?

436
00:20:07,989 --> 00:20:09,991
- Well, I can do
a catheter ablation.

437
00:20:10,034 --> 00:20:11,297
It'll destroy the source
of the problem.

438
00:20:11,340 --> 00:20:12,428
It's non-surgical.

439
00:20:12,472 --> 00:20:13,603
You won't even have
to be put under.

440
00:20:13,647 --> 00:20:15,388
- NASA has run
hundreds of tests on me.

441
00:20:15,431 --> 00:20:17,128
How did they miss this?

442
00:20:17,172 --> 00:20:19,130
- It might be the first time
it happened.

443
00:20:19,174 --> 00:20:20,610
- Will it happen again?

444
00:20:20,654 --> 00:20:22,264
- It's hard to tell.
It might.

445
00:20:22,308 --> 00:20:23,439
- It won't.

446
00:20:23,483 --> 00:20:25,702
We came here last-minute
for family.

447
00:20:25,746 --> 00:20:28,575
I just need to get back
to Houston, back to training.

448
00:20:28,618 --> 00:20:30,054
- Mack.

449
00:20:30,098 --> 00:20:32,274
- NASA said I'm fine,
so I'm fine.

450
00:20:34,624 --> 00:20:37,148
- Um, Mackenzie,

451
00:20:37,192 --> 00:20:41,152
the attack you had today
probably lasted a few seconds,

452
00:20:41,196 --> 00:20:44,199
but a serious one
could last a few minutes,

453
00:20:44,243 --> 00:20:46,288
maybe even hours.

454
00:20:46,332 --> 00:20:47,768
And instead of losing control
of your bladder,

455
00:20:47,811 --> 00:20:50,336
you could lose consciousness.

456
00:20:50,379 --> 00:20:52,555
If that happens
while you're in space,

457
00:20:52,599 --> 00:20:55,210
your whole mission
could be compromised.

458
00:20:55,254 --> 00:20:57,473
You could risk the lives
of your crew.

459
00:20:57,517 --> 00:20:59,519
- I would never do that.

460
00:20:59,562 --> 00:21:01,651
- Then don't walk out of here.

461
00:21:04,785 --> 00:21:07,396
- If I do this procedure,
will I still be cleared to fly?

462
00:21:07,440 --> 00:21:08,789
- If it's successful,

463
00:21:08,832 --> 00:21:11,313
this will take care
of the problem permanently.

464
00:21:11,357 --> 00:21:12,706
After a period of observation,

465
00:21:12,749 --> 00:21:14,360
I don't see a reason why
you'd be grounded.

466
00:21:17,450 --> 00:21:18,755
- You got this.

467
00:21:21,541 --> 00:21:24,761
- Paz, I have your scan results

468
00:21:24,805 --> 00:21:26,633
from this morning.

469
00:21:26,676 --> 00:21:29,418
Your tumor has stopped
responding to the chemo.

470
00:21:32,334 --> 00:21:34,075
To prevent it from spreading,

471
00:21:34,118 --> 00:21:36,295
